body:
@davebaol Yes, that log does always show the wrong text.

I've made some progress. Looks like this isn't a font or localisation issue. It's a file loading / encoding issue. I still can't work out why it's happening (I've triple checked my files are UTF-8). I use the following code to replicate what the I18NBundle class does and log the file contents. The text is not the same as the original file. The loaded and logged file shows the same errors that the translation shows. I'll update the github project to include this.

```
private void logFileContents() {
    // Load bundle properties from the stream with the specified encoding
    FileHandle file = Gdx.files.internal("Local/Local_ru.properties");
    Reader reader = file.reader("UTF-8");
    BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(reader);

    StringBuilder fileContents = new StringBuilder();
    String line;
    try {
        while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
            fileContents.append(line + "\r\n");
        }
    } catch (IOException e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    }

    Gdx.app.log("File", fileContents.toString());
}
```

Just to confirm, if I download the file in the browser then it does show the correct contents.

I'm gradually narrowing this down. Below in an updated logFileContents method.

The first log creates a string from the raw file bytes, this outputs the file correctly. String created by `br.readLine()` is incorrect, so it looks to me like the UTF-8 decoding in `BufferedReader` is buggy. This seems like a fairly critical bug to exist in GWT however, so am I misunderstanding something? If I'm right, then it looks like there's not much that can be done about it in libgdx. The only thing I can think of off the top of my head is if the encoding is UTF-8, then call `new String(bytes)` to get the char array and process that rather than reading char by char with the `BufferedReader`.

```
private void logFileContents() {
    // Load bundle properties from the stream with the specified encoding
    FileHandle file = Gdx.files.internal("Local/Local_ru.properties");

    byte[] bytes = file.readBytes();

    String test = new String(bytes);
    Gdx.app.log("File", test);

    Reader reader = file.reader("UTF-8");
    BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(reader);

    StringBuilder fileContents = new StringBuilder();
    String line;
    try {
        while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
            Gdx.app.log("Line", line);
            fileContents.append(line + "\r\n");
        }
    } catch (IOException e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    }

    Gdx.app.log("File", fileContents.toString());
}
```
